# This app collects source/target credentials directly in the UI at
# runtime, so no server-side secrets are strictly required.
#
# If you'd rather pre-fill the form (e.g. for a single, fixed org) you can
# read NEXT_PUBLIC_-prefixed values from here in TransferConsole.tsx — but
# never put a client secret in a NEXT_PUBLIC_ variable, since those are
# shipped to the browser. Keep secrets server-side or entered per-session.

# Example, non-secret defaults you could wire up:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DEFAULT_DATABASE=master
